\[f^{\prime}(2) = \lim_{h\to 0}\frac{f\left(2+h\right)-f\left(2\right)}{h}=\lim_{h \to 0}\frac{3\left(2+h\right)-3\left(2\right)}{h}\] \[\cdot\] \[= \lim_{h\to 0}\frac{6+3h-6}{h}=\lim_{h\to 0}\frac{3h}{h}=\lim_{h\to 0}3=3.\]

The derivative of the function \(3x\) at \(x=2\) is \(3\).

