\[C = (A-A^{\prime})^{\prime}=A^{\prime}-(A^{\prime})^{\prime}\text{ (Why?)}\] \[= A^{\prime}-A\text{ (Why?)}\] \[= -(A-A^{\prime})=-C\]

Therefore \(C=A-A^{\prime}\) is a skew symmetric matrix.

**Theorem 2**: Any square matrix can be expressed as the sum of a symmetric and a skew symmetric matrix.

