### Minors and Cofactors

In this section, we will learn to write the expansion of a determinant in compact form using minors and cofactors.

**Definition 1** Minor of an element \(a_{{}_{\!g}}\) of a determinant is the determinant obtained by deleting its \(i\)th row and \(j\)th column in which element \(a_{{}_{\!g}}\) lies. Minor of an element \(a_{{}_{\!g}}\) is denoted by \(\mathrm{M}_{{}_{\!g}}\).

_Remark_ Minor of an element of a determinant of order \(n(n\geq 2)\) is a determinant of order \(n-1\).

**Example 8** Find the minor of element 6 in the determinant \(\Delta=\begin{array}{c|cc}1&2&3\\ 4&5&6\\ 7&8&9\end{array}\)

**Solution** Since 6 lies in the second row and third column, its minor \(\mathrm{M}_{{}_{\!23}}\) is given by

