\[\mathop{\lim}\limits_{x\to 0}f(x)=\lim_{x\to 0}x^{2}=0^{2}=0\]

Thus \(\mathop{\lim}\limits_{x\to 0}f(x)=0=f(0)\)

Hence, \(f\) is continuous at \(x=0\).

