If we have two vectors \(\vec{a}\) and \(\vec{b}\) represented by the two adjacent sides of a parallelogram in magnitude and direction (Fig 10.9), then their sum \(\vec{a}+\vec{b}\) is represented in magnitude and direction by the diagonal of the parallelogram through their common point. This is known as the _parallelogram law of vector addition._

