**Properties of vector addition**

**Property 1**: For any two vectors \(\vec{a}\) and \(\vec{b}\),

\[\vec{a}+\vec{b}=\vec{b}+\vec{a}\] (Commutative property)

**Proof** Consider the parallelogram ABCD (Fig 10.10). Let \(\overline{\text{AB}}=\bar{a}\) and \(\overline{\text{BC}}=\bar{b}\), then using the triangle law, from triangle ABC, we have

\[\overline{\text{AC}}=\bar{a}+\bar{b}\]

